   36: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
   37: %% Initializations
   38: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
   39: 
   40: %-define(dont_rm_test_dirs, true).
   41: 
   42: -ifndef(dont_rm_test_dirs).
   43: 
   44: init_per_suite(Config) ->
   45:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   46:     ok=erl_tar:extract("ibm.tgz",[compressed]),
   47:     ok=erl_tar:extract("japanese.tgz",[compressed]),
   48:     ok=erl_tar:extract("oasis.tgz",[compressed]),
   49:     ok=erl_tar:extract("sun.tgz",[compressed]),
   50:     ok=erl_tar:extract("xmltest.tgz",[compressed]),
   51:     ok = change_mode(["ibm","japanese","oasis",
   52:                       "sun","xmltest"]),
   53:     [{timetrap,{seconds, 1}}|Config].
   54: 
   55: end_per_suite(Config) ->
   56:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   57:     ok=rm_files(["ibm","japanese","oasis","sun","xmltest"]),
   58:     Config.
   59: 
   60: -else.
   61: 
   62: init_per_suite(Config) ->
   63:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
   64:     [{timetrap,{seconds, 1}}|Config].
   65: 
   66: end_per_suite(Config) ->
   67:     Config.
   68: 
   69: -endif.
   70: 
   71: %% initialization before each testcase
   72: init_per_testcase(_TestCase,Config) ->
   73:     io:format("Config:\n~p\n",[Config]),
   74:     {ok, _} = file:read_file_info(filename:join([privdir(Config)])),
   75:     code:add_patha(privdir(Config)),
   76:     Config.
   77:  
   78: %% clean up after each testcase
   79: end_per_testcase(_Func,_Config) ->
   80:     ok.
   81:

   95: %% Type: not-wf
   96: %% Sections: 3.1 [41]
   97: %% Description:
   98: %%   Attribute values must start with attribute names, not "?".
   99: 'not-wf-sa-001'(Config) -> 
  100:     file:set_cwd(datadir(Config)),
  101:     Path = filename:join([datadir(Config),"xmltest","not-wf/sa/001.xml"]),
  102:     R = xmerl_sax_parser:file(Path, [{event_fun, fun sax_canon/3}]),
  103:     check_result(R, "not-wf").

29493: init_per_group(_GroupName, Config) ->
29494:     Config.
29495: 
29496: end_per_group(_GroupName, Config) ->
29497:     Config.
29498: 
29499: %%======================================================================
29500: %% Support Functions
29501: %%======================================================================
29502: 
29503: %% Dir is a directory
29504: rm_f_(Dir) ->
29505:     {ok,CWD} = file:get_cwd(),
29506:     {ok,FileList} = file:list_dir(Dir),
29507:     file:set_cwd(filename:join([CWD,Dir])),
29508:     rm_files(FileList),
29509:     file:set_cwd(CWD),
29510:     ? line ok = file:del_dir(Dir).
29511: 
29512: rm_files([])->
29513:     ok;
29514: rm_files([F|Fs]) ->
29515:     case filelib:is_dir(F) of
29516:     true ->
29517:         rm_f_(F);
29518:     _ ->
29519:         ok = file:delete(F)
29520:     end,
29521:     rm_files(Fs).
29522: 
29523: 
29524: change_mode(Files) ->
29525:     change_mode3(Files).
29526: change_mode2(Dir)->
29527:     {ok,CWD} = file:get_cwd(),
29528:     {ok,FileList} = file:list_dir(Dir),
29529:     file:set_cwd(filename:join([CWD,Dir])),
29530:     change_mode3(FileList),
29531:     file:set_cwd(CWD).
29532: change_mode3([]) ->
29533:     ok;
29534: change_mode3([F|Fs]) ->
29535:     case filelib:is_dir(F) of
29536:     true ->
29537:         chmod(F),
29538:         change_mode2(F);
29539:     _ ->
29540:         chmod(F)
29541:     end,
29542:     change_mode3(Fs).
29543:     
29544: chmod(F) ->
29545:     case file:read_file_info(F) of
29546:     {ok,FileInfo} ->
29547:         Mode= FileInfo#file_info.mode,
29548:         file:write_file_info(F,FileInfo#file_info{mode=8#00777 bor Mode});
29549:     _ ->
29550:         ok
29551:     end.
29552: 
29553: privdir(Config) ->
29554:     proplists:get_value(priv_dir, Config).
29555: datadir(Config) ->
29556:     proplists:get_value(data_dir, Config).
29557: 
29558: %%----------------------------------------------------------------------
29559: %% check_result 
29560: check_result({fatal_error,_,_,_,_}, "error") -> ok;
29561: check_result({ok, _, _}, "invalid") -> ok;
29562: check_result({fatal_error,_,_,_,_}, "not-wf") -> ok;
29563: check_result({ok, _, _}, "valid") -> ok;
29564: check_result(A, T) -> ct:fail({2, T, A}).
29565: 
29566: check_result({ok, B, _}, "invalid", B) -> ok;
29567: check_result({ok, B, _}, "valid", B) -> ok;
29568: check_result({ok, B, _}, "error", B) -> ok;
29569: check_result(A, T, B) -> ct:fail({3, T, A, B}).
29570: 
29571: sax_canon({startElement, _, _, {Prefix, LocalName}, Attributes},_,{S, Es}) ->
29572:        LName = unicode:characters_to_binary(LocalName),
29573:        Name = case Prefix of
29574:              [] ->
29575:                 LName;
29576:              _ ->
29577:                 Px = unicode:characters_to_binary(Prefix),
29578:                 <<Px/binary, $:, LName/binary>>
29579:           end,
29580:        Atts = <<
29581:             begin
29582:                 AName = 
29583:                     case APrefix of
29584:                         [] -> 
29585:                             unicode:characters_to_binary(AttributeName);
29586:                         _ ->
29587:                             P = unicode:characters_to_binary(APrefix),
29588:                             L = unicode:characters_to_binary(AttributeName),
29589:                             <<P/binary, $:, L/binary>>
29590:                     end,
29591:                 Val = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Value)),
29592:                 <<" ", AName/binary, "=\"", Val/binary, "\"">>
29593:             end
29594:             ||
29595:             {_, APrefix, AttributeName, Value} <- lists:sort(Attributes)
29596:             >>,
29597:        {<<S/binary, $<, Name/binary, Atts/binary, $>>>, [element|Es]};
29598: sax_canon({endElement, _, _, {Prefix, LocalName}},_, {S, [_|Es]}) ->
29599:        LName = unicode:characters_to_binary(LocalName),
29600:        Name = case Prefix of
29601:              [] ->
29602:                 LName;
29603:              _ ->
29604:                 Px = unicode:characters_to_binary(Prefix),
29605:                 <<Px/binary, $:, LName/binary>>
29606:           end,
29607:        {<<S/binary, "</" , Name/binary, ">">>, Es};
29608: sax_canon({characters, Str},_,{S, Es}) -> 
29609:     Bin = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Str)),
29610:     {<<S/binary, Bin/binary>>, Es};
29611: sax_canon({ignorableWhitespace, Str},_,{S, [element|_] = Es}) -> 
29612:     Bin = norm_chars(unicode:characters_to_binary(Str)),
29613:     {<<S/binary, Bin/binary>>, Es};
29614: sax_canon({processingInstruction, Target, Data},_,{S, Es}) -> 
29615:     T = unicode:characters_to_binary(Target),
29616:     case Data of
29617:            [] ->
29618:               {<<S/binary, "<?", T/binary, " ?>">>, Es};
29619:            _ ->
29620:               D = unicode:characters_to_binary(Data),
29621:               {<<S/binary, "<?", T/binary, " ", D/binary, "?>">>, Es}
29622:     end;
29623: sax_canon(startDocument,_,_) -> {<<>>, []};
29624: sax_canon(endDocument,_,{S, _}) -> S;
29625: sax_canon({startDTD, _, _, _} = E,_,{S, []}) -> {S, [E]};
29626: sax_canon(endDTD,_,{S, Es}) -> 
29627:     % report any notations
29628:     case Es of
29629:         [_] ->
29630:             {S, []};
29631:         _ ->
29632:            [{startDTD, Name, _PublicId, _SystemId}|Ns] = lists:reverse(Es),
29633:            F = fun({notationDecl, NName, PublicId, []}) ->
29634:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29635:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(PublicId),
29636:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " PUBLIC '", BId/binary, "'>">>;
29637:                   ({notationDecl, NName, [], SystemId}) ->
29638:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29639:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(SystemId),
29640:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " SYSTEM '", BId/binary, "'>">>;
29641:                   ({notationDecl, NName, PublicId, SystemId}) ->
29642:                      BNName = unicode:characters_to_binary(NName),
29643:                      PId = unicode:characters_to_binary(PublicId),
29644:                      BId = unicode:characters_to_binary(SystemId),
29645:                      <<"\n<!NOTATION ", BNName/binary, " PUBLIC '", PId/binary, "' '", BId/binary, "'>">>
29646:                end,
29647:            Sort = fun({_,A,_,_},{_,B,_,_}) -> A =< B end,
29648:            Nots = iolist_to_binary(lists:map(F, lists:sort(Sort, Ns))),
29649:            DName = unicode:characters_to_binary(Name),
29650:            Db = <<S/binary, "<!DOCTYPE ", DName/binary, " [",
29651:                   Nots/binary,
29652:                   "\n]>\n">>,
29653:            {Db, []}
29654:     end;
29655: sax_canon({notationDecl, _, _, _} = E,_,{S, Es}) -> 
29656:    {S, [E|Es]};
29657: sax_canon(_,_,S) -> S.
29658: 
29659: norm_chars(Bin) ->
29660:     <<
29661:     case C of
29662:         9 -> <<"&#9;">>;
29663:         10 -> <<"&#10;">>;
29664:         13 -> <<"&#13;">>;
29665:         $< -> <<"&lt;">>;
29666:         $> -> <<"&gt;">>;
29667:         38 -> <<"&amp;">>;
29668:         $" -> <<"&quot;">>;
29669:         _ ->
29670:            <<C/utf8>>
29671:     end || <<C/utf8>> <= Bin >>.
